<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<activity xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-2-1-constants-truck">
    <statement>
        <p>
            It's always useful to explain in everyday words what the constants in an equation mean in the story. The two constants in the story about the truck hauling bags of grass seed are 3,900 and 4.2.
        </p>
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>
                <p>
                    What units does the 3,900 have? What does it mean in the story?
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    What units does the 4.2 have? What does it mean in the story?
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Which one of these constants is the <term>intercept</term> (or <term>start</term>)? Which one is the <term>slope</term>?
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
</activity>